T1  - Heterogeneous creditors and the market value of bank LDC loan portfolios
AU  - James, Christopher
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 25
IS  - 3
SP  - 325
EP  - 346
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/06/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(90)90057-B
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439329090057B
AB  - A standard proposition used in many empirical studies is that the value of an LDC loan does not depend on the identity of the lender. I test this proposition using bank securities prices and prices for LDC loans trading in the secondary market. I find significant cross-sectional differences in the sensitivity of bank stocks to changes in the price of LDC loans. Differences in sensitivity appear to be related to changes in bank exposure to LDCs. I also find evidence consistent with the hypothesis that CDs are implicitly insured.
ER  - 

