T1  - The optimal inflation path in a Sidrauski-type model with uncertainty
AU  - Den Haan, Wouter J.
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 25
IS  - 3
SP  - 389
EP  - 409
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/06/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(90)90060-H
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439329090060H
AB  - In this paper it is shown that in a Sidrauski-type model with uncertainty, the Chicago Rule remains valid as a prescription for the average rate of inflation, although there is a systematic difference between the perfect-foresight and the uncertainty case. Quantitatively, however, the difference turns out to be very small. The paper shows how to calculate the optimal monetary policy as a function of the state variables using the method of parameterized expectations. In terms of expected utility, the optimal policy is as good as the simple policy that reduces the money supply at the rate of time preference.
ER  - 

